#. type: Title #
#: ../src/cookbook/using-htmx-for-partial-reloads.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using htmx for partial page reloads"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/using-htmx-for-partial-reloads.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[htmx](https://htmx.org/) lets links and forms request HTML fragments and swap them into the current page. In a Yii\n"
"application, this works well for grids: sorting, filtering, and pagination can update only the grid while the rest of\n"
"the page stays in place.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/using-htmx-for-partial-reloads.md
msgid "This recipe uses `GridView` as an example because it has links and forms that naturally benefit from partial reloads.  The same pattern works for any widget or page fragment: render the fragment separately, add htmx attributes to the controls that should refresh it, and return only that fragment for htmx requests."
msgstr ""

